  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: Geth/v1.10.16-stable/linux-amd64/go1.16.5`\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 20.04.2 LTS\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nTo avoid mining empty blocks, I set 'noempty' flag to 1 in the \"worker\" structure in /miner/worker.go. This used to work.\r\n// noempty is the flag used to control whether the feature of pre-seal empty\r\n// block is enabled. The default value is false(pre-seal is enabled by default).\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nStopped working starting from v1.10.16.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nSet 'noempty' flag to 1 in the \"worker\" structure in /miner/worker.go, compile, start geth with --mine and check for \"Commit new sealing work\" with txs=0 in output.\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\n[backtrace]\r\n````\r\n\r\nWhen submitting logs: please submit them as text and not screenshots.",
